title: Canada agrees to ISS extension to 2030
summary: The Canadian government formally committed March 24 to an extension of the International Space Station to 2030, joining other Western partners but not Russia.

title: OneWeb set to complete initial constellation with launch from India
summary: OneWeb is set to finish its initial satellite constellation buildout, as India and its space agency, the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO), prepares to make its second orbital flight of 2023 by flying 36 of the company’s satellites aboard its LVM3 (previously known as the GSLV Mk III) launch vehicle from the Satish Dhawan Space Centre.

title: Dawn Aerospace's Spaceplane Gets Green Light for Suborbital Test Flights in New Zealand
summary: New Zealand-based aerospace company, Dawn Aerospace, has received certification from the New Zealand Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) for its Mk-II Aurora spaceplane's rocket-powered flight campaign. The Mk-II Aurora's mission is to fly twice to space in a day, demonstrating that rocket-powered systems can be as reusable as commercial aircraft.

title: Space companies Spire and Momentus get stock exchange delisting warnings
summary: A pair of space companies received delisting warnings on Friday, according to securities filings, as both ventures’ stock prices stood below $1 a share.

title: NASA Invites Media to See Mars Habitat Before Crew Enters for One Year
summary: Media are invited to visit NASA’s simulated Mars habitat on Tuesday, April 11, at the agency’s Johnson Space Center in Houston. This summer, four volunteers will begin a yearlong Mars mission in the ground-based habitat, helping NASA prepare for human exploration of Mars for the benefit of humanity.

title: Rocket Lab targets $50 million launch price for Neutron rocket to challenge SpaceX’s Falcon 9
summary: Rocket Lab is building a bigger, reusable launch vehicle called Neutron, and it’s targeting a price point near $50 million per launch to challenge Elon Musk’s SpaceX.

title: Blue Origin blames New Shepard mishap on engine nozzle failure
summary: Blue Origin says it is preparing to resume flights of its New Shepard suborbital vehicle after completing an investigation into a failed launch last September.

title: NASA Coverage Set for Uncrewed Soyuz Undocking, Departure
summary: The uncrewed Roscosmos Soyuz MS-22 spacecraft will undock from the International Space Station on Tuesday, March 28.

title: ABL Space gets $60 million for responsive launch demonstrations
summary: WASHINGTON — ABL Space Systems, a California-based launch startup, announced March 24 it has secured a $60 million contract from the U.S. Space Force and U.S. Air Force that also includes matching funds from private investors, a type of agreement known as strategic funding increase, or STRATFI.  The contract is for ground and flight demonstrations […]

title: Cape Congestion: World’s busiest spaceport stretched to its limits
summary: Cape Canaveral’s infrastructure is being stretched to its limits as the world’s busiest launch site continues to get busier.
